Author::::SittingDown
DateTime::::2016-03-09T17:25:40Z
'Physical lane segregation is divisive, ill-though-out and wasteful'I disagree with the above comment. On the divisive note - well that is the actual intention - the word segregated offers a clue here. Apologies for the sarcasm but that is the point of them. On major routes and in certain other instances they make complete and utter sense. A painted line is better than nothing but is simply a painted line. I cycle on such routes all the time and continually experience motor vehicles moving across the lines and often parking on them. In some areas of my city (Brighton & Hove) there is almost permanent parking in certain sections so in effect they are no longer cycle lanes. Consideration needs to be given to those less able, the younger and older cyclists and those with less experience. If we want to give everyone the chance to cycle safely in their city I think separating the cyclist from the cars, buses and lorries is an intelligent concept.



