Author::::ComfortablyPlumb
DateTime::::2016-03-09T16:02:37Z
Certainly not. With presumed liability, if there is evidence that the other party caused the accident the driver will not be held liable. The default, where there is no evidence either way, is that the driver's insurance will pay compensation. That's what insurance is for. At present where there is no evidence, there may be no compensation for someone who has been seriously injured.



